                                 <p>That the first party, IGCPL, through its G-Plus and G-Laabh services is engaged in the activity of providing channel-partner services, logistics fulfilment services, coordination towards GeM supplies, showroom/retail/ wholesale of the products of the various sellers under the IGCPL schemes of G-Laabh and G-Plus, and related services, on chargeable basis, and the seller cash-flow management services through G-Cash division of IGCPL.  That the second party is desirous of availing the services offered by the first party as per the terms of this MoU. </p>
                                 <p>That<strong> ___(name of 2nd Party) _____, </strong>the second party and IGCPL, the second party are desirous of entering into a Memorandum of Understanding to avail and provide the services of channel-partnership, fulfilment services, coordination towards GeM supplies, showroom/retail/ wholesale of the products of the second party,<strong> _______ </strong> under the IGCPL schemes of G-Laabh and G-Plus on chargeable basis, as well as the G-cash services of cash flow management as per the terms and conditions of the G-cash division. </p>
                                 <p>Now therefore, the first party, IGCPL and the second party<strong> _____(name of 2nd Party)_________ </strong> have decided to enter into this memorandum of understanding, initially for one year upon onboarding, further extendable annually on terms and conditions enumerated in this document, subject to renewal of onboarding by the first party upon mutual consent. The MoU will be valid year after year upon fulfilment of terms and conditions by either party, and upon mutual understanding.</p>
                                 <p><strong> Common terms and Statements: </strong> In this document, unless otherwise specified, the following shall be understood from the words/ clauses/ acronyms used in various places <b>:</b></p>
                                 <ul>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>1. IGCPL: </strong> M/s Indigem Channel Partner Private Limited which intends to provide G-Laabh and G-Plus scheme services to various Seller/sellers/ vendors in India and abroad on chargeable basis.</li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>2. GeM: </strong> The Government e-marketplace scheme wherein Government organizations and Sellers interact to purchase and sell items.</li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>3. Supplier/Seller/Vendor: </strong> Any Vendor registered with GeM/ outside GeM who is engaged in manufacturing/ Trading/ manufacturing cum-trading/ authorised dealer/ Original equipment manufacturer, who supplies its goods/services/items, etc. to government organization on GeM/ others outside GeM and intends to avail the services of IGCPL.</li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>4. Purchaser/Buyer/ Consignee: </strong> Any Government organization which is engaged in procuring items from Sellers on the GeM platform/ non-GeM platform; Any private entity which is procuring items from Sellers in open market.</li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>5. Trust based services: </strong> The items being procured and supplied shall be as per the terms of agreement between the purchaser and the Seller; IGCPL shall merely assist in delivery and post-delivery coordination under Trust based services. IGCPL shall have no roles and responsibilities in determination of authenticity of product/dimensions/ quality of product/ rates of product, etc. IGCPL shall only market, pick-pack-deliver the products of Seller to the designated buyer on GeM/ outside GeM. Further, IGCPL shall not be responsible for any disputes between GeM authorities and the Seller, or the Buyer on compliance, or otherwise of the policies of GeM, or on any matter amongst these entities. </li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>6. G-Laabh scheme: </strong> Under this scheme IGCPL shall provide to the Sellers (doing their business on GeM portal/Outside GeM portal and desirous of on-boarding the Channel-partner program of IGCPL), on chargeable basis, the services of delivery-coordination, Sample-clause coordination, CRAC generation, Bill clearance/Bill discounting services coordination, all other co-ordination services required to fulfil the work-order of Client till settlement of bills. </li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>7. G-Plus scheme: </strong>  Under this scheme IGCPL shall provide logistics fulfilment services of pick-pack and delivery; staggered delivery; maintenance of local-sample showrooms; retail and whole sale services to local/regional areas all across India on chargeable basis. The Sellers shall ensure that the comparable sale-prices for retail/wholesale are higher than the prices they offer on GeM portal, in accordance with the GeM policies. IGCPL shall not be responsible for any violation of Seller in this regard. </li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>8. G-Cash scheme: </strong> IGCPL intends to support GeM-registered Sellers/ other Sellers in invoice discounting/ Bill Discounting/ factor discounting/ cash management services at most economical rates, once the CRAC formalities are completed at Buyer’s end and there is no dispute on the product between the seller and the buyer. The Sellers who onboard IGCPL can avail these services at most economical rates. </li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>9. G-café scheme: </strong> Another scheme of IGCPL wherein GeM- assistance services shall be offered to sellers/ buyers on piecemeal/ six-monthly/ annual contract basis. A resourceful team of IGCPL shall maintain café at multiple locations in India. The Buyers and Sellers can avail the services of experts for registration, sales, purchase, etc. on GeM. Under G-café scheme, the buyer/ seller can also outsource their GeM Sales/ purchase services to the G-café team. The onboarding and the charges shall be governed by a separate MoU. </li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>10.   G-Laabh and G-Plus services shall be outside the platform and purview of GeM: </strong> Under the G-Laabh and G-Plus schemes, IGCPL, as channel partner, shall assist the sellers outside the platform and purview of GeM. It will commence its work upon receipt of ‘Work-order’ from the Seller, alongwith a copy of GeM portal generated Work-order of any buyer organization. The Seller and Buyers shall be responsible at all times towards GeM and shall keep IGCPL indemnified at all times. All communication on GeM platform shall be between the buyer and the seller. IGCPL shall assist and take responsibility for the fulfilment services, delivery, post-delivery coordination, sample-clause coordination, staggered-supplies and bill-clearance; and cash flow management for such sellers who opt for it, on case-to-case basis. IGCPL shall have no stake or responsibility in the dealings of the sellers and Buyers on the GeM platform. </li>
                                    <li class="my-2"><strong>11.   Onboarding: </strong> The act of GeM Registered Seller whereby it submits necessary documents, details of Bank account, agrees to terms and conditions of this MoU, makes payment of annual onboarding fee, opens an account with IGCPL website/app and agrees to appoint IGCPL as its Channel partner for the services offered by IGCPL, as described in this MoU document. </li>
