                                    <li class="my-2">1.   IGCPL shall provide channel-partnership services to the second party in various cities of India under its G-Laabh and G-Plus scheme, which interalia, shall comprise of the following services provided to the onboarded channel partner on chargeable basis:</li>
                                    <ul>
                                       <li class="my-2">a. IGCPL shall establish its local offices in multiple cities of India where Government organizations are located who purchase their requirements from sellers through the GeM portal of the Government of India. </li>
                                       <li class="my-2">b. IGCPL shall onboard the Sellers desirous of availing “channel-partner- cum- fulfilment-cum Sample showroom- cum retail/wholesale services” being offered by IGCPL. The supplier shall authorise IGCPL to act as its authorised-agent for marketing, sales, supply, CRAC coordination, sample clause coordination, billing coordination, delivery coordination, staggered supply coordination, etc on chargeable basis. </li>
                                       <li class="my-2">c. IGCPL shall co-ordinate the pick, pack & delivery of items after generation of work-order in GeM/ outside Gem purchasers; coordinate for CRAC/receipt; Coordinate submission of Bills and payment to the Sellers from government/ non-Government buyers. </li>
