                                       <li class="my-2">f. IGCPL, on its own or through its associates, may also offer Bill-discounting services to Sellers at competitive rates on due diligence, to only such sellers who are desirous of availing such services on chargeable basis, under G-cash scheme. </li>
                                       <li class="my-2">g. IGCPL, within the next 24 months, aims to open about 40-50 sample stores across India. IGCPL shall maintain local show-room for major items of sellers, being supplied through GeM with an aim to provide services of sample-viewing to Government organizations desirous of procuring such items. By maintaining small-stocks of inventory in sample showrooms, the Seller can participate in low-volume work-orders with buyers who are located far and wide. The sellers can also participate in purchase work-orders wherein ‘sample clause’ is invoked by the buyer.</li>
                                       <li class="my-2">h. IGCPL shall provide services of ‘Return to origin’ in cases where the Buyer rejects the supplied items on chargeable basis. </li>
                                       <li class="my-2">i. Local to Global scheme: IGCPL shall market the products of sellers in markets all over India with an aim to provide the onboarded partners a country-wide market.</li>
                                       <li class="my-2">j. Any other ancillary services upon mutual written communication between the onboarded client and IGCPL.
