                                       <li class="my-2">f. The Seller shall transmit an authentic Work-order to IGCPL. IGCPL shall promptly generate Fulfilment estimate and issue a demand note to Seller. Upon payment/agreement on the modalities of payment and delivery with the Seller, IGCPL shall ensure fulfilment delivery to the Buyer in accordance with the Work-order.</li>
                                       <li class="my-2">g. The Seller shall promptly clear its dues, or agree to the arrangement wherein IGCPL shall deduct its charges as per the Invoice raised on Seller. The Seller agrees to maintain an escrow account with IGCPL for the purpose of receipt of GeM payment from Buyer. The Seller agrees to pay 50% of the Logistics/ Fulfilment charges in advance. Alternately, the Seller can maintain a lumpsum deposit in the Escrow account, as a security towards fulfilment/logistics charges, instead of making advance payments. All due fee/payments/charges will be deducted from the Discounted Bill payments/ Final settlement of Bill payment as per invoice raised on the Seller. The responsibility of compliance with the Income Tax/ GST TDS clauses shall be of the Seller. The Seller shall also issue TDS certificates to IGCPL. </li>
                                       <li class="my-2">h. The Seller shall issue a certificate appointing IGCPL as its channel partners on pan-India basis authorizing the first party to store, deal with, market and undertake sales of its product to interested buyers at mutually agreed prices.</li>
